---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
---
<Base title="Privacy — Foot Morning America" description="How Foot Morning America handles data: minimal collection, privacy-friendly analytics, no email lists.">
  <section class="mx-auto max-w-2xl py-10">
    <h1 class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl">Privacy Policy</h1>
    <div class="article-body mt-6">
      <p>Foot Morning America keeps things simple: we collect as little as possible.</p>
      <p><strong>No accounts, no email lists.</strong> We don't ask you to sign up, and we don't run a
        newsletter or collect email addresses from visitors.</p>
      <p><strong>Analytics.</strong> We may use privacy-friendly, cookie-less analytics (such as
        Cloudflare Web Analytics) to count visits in aggregate. It does not track you across sites or
        build a profile of you.</p>
      <p><strong>Creator submissions.</strong> If you submit a listing via "Get Featured," we store the
        details you provide (display name, handle, link, optional photo and bio) to review and, if
        approved, publish them. Don't submit anything you don't want shown publicly.</p>
      <p><strong>Outbound &amp; affiliate links.</strong> When you click a link to a third-party platform,
        that site's own privacy policy applies. Some outbound links are affiliate links, meaning we may
        earn a commission at no cost to you.</p>
      <p><strong>Questions or removal requests?</strong> See our <a href="/legal/dmca">content &amp;
        removal policy</a>, or contact <span class="dateline">legal@footmorningamerica.com</span>.</p>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>
